1 (c) (d) "Rack" means a mechanism for delivering refined
2 petroleum or a refined petroleum product from a refiner, a pipeline
3 terminal operator, or a marine terminal operator into a railroad
4 tank car, a transport truck, a tank wagon, or the fuel supply tank
5 of a marine vessel.
6 (d) (e) "Refined petroleum" means aviation gasoline, middle
7 distillates, jet fuel, kerosene, gasoline, residual oils, and any
8 oxygenates that have been blended with any of these. Refined
9 petroleum includes refined petroleum products and transmix. Refined
10 petroleum does not include excluded liquids.
11 (e) (f) "Refined petroleum fund" means the refined petroleum
12 fund established under section 21506a.
13 (f) (g) "Refined petroleum underground storage tank" means an
14 underground storage tank system used for the storage of refined
15 petroleum.
