8 Sec. 21510. (1) An owner or operator is eligible to receive
9 money from the authority for corrective action or indemnification
10 due to a confirmed release from a refined petroleum underground
11 storage tank system only if all of the following requirements are
12 satisfied and the owner or operator otherwise complies with this
13 part:
14 (a) The release from which the corrective action or
15 indemnification arose was discovered and reported on or after
16 December 30, 2014.
17 (b) The refined petroleum underground storage tank from which
18 the release occurred was, at the time of discovery of the release ,
19 and is presently, in compliance with the registration and fee
20 requirements of part 211. The refined petroleum underground storage
21 tank owned by a federally recognized tribe from which the release
22 occurred was, at the time of discovery of the release, in
23 compliance with federal registration and fee requirements.
24 (c) The owner or operator reported the confirmed release
25 within not later than 24 hours after its discovery as required by
26 part 211 and the rules promulgated under that part.of the confirmed
27 release.
28 (d) The owner or operator is not the United States government.
29 (e) The claim is not for a release from a refined petroleum
