14
1 for corrective action or indemnification due to a release that
2 originates from an aboveground piping and dispensing portion of a
3 refined petroleum underground storage tank system if all of the
4 following requirements are satisfied:
5 (a) The owner or operator is otherwise in compliance with this
6 part and the rules promulgated under this part.
7 (b) The release is sudden and immediate.
8 (c) The release is of a quantity exceeding 25 gallons and is
9 released into groundwater, surface water, or soils.
10 (d) The owner or operator reported the release to the
11 department within 24 hours after its discovery.
12 (2) (3) Either the owner or the operator may receive money
13 from the authority under this part for an occurrence, but not both.
14 (3) (4) An owner or operator that is a public utility with
15 more than 500,000 customers in this state is ineligible to receive
16 money from the authority for corrective action or indemnification
17 associated with a release from a refined petroleum underground
18 storage tank system used to supply refined petroleum for the
19 generation of steam electricity.
20 (5) If an owner or operator has received money from the
