10 (d) A release arising from a consequence, whether direct or
11 indirect, of war, invasion, act of a foreign enemy, act of
12 terrorists, hostilities, whether war has been declared or not,
13 civil war, rebellion, revolution, insurrection, usurpation of
14 power, strike, riot, or civil commotion.
15 Enacting section 1. Section 21510c of the natural resources
16 and environmental protection act, 1994 PA 451, MCL 324.21510c, is
17 repealed.
18 Enacting section 2. This amendatory act does not take effect
19 unless House Bill No. 5115 of the 103rd Legislature is enacted into
20 law.
